cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the application of low-dimensional vector space representations to knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also discusses the compatibility between ontological knowledge and vector space embeddings, which is relevant to the subfield of databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper addresses the logical consistency and deductive closure of the induced set of facts, which is related to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR).
